import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='ret', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['ret'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['ret'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of daily returns?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Daily Returns")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='open', y='close', hue='signal', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between open and close prices?', wrap=True)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    avg_ret_by_signal = data.groupby('signal')['ret'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='signal', y='ret', data=avg_ret_by_signal)
    chart.set_title('What is the average daily return for each signal type?')
    chart.set_ylabel('Average Daily Return')
    chart.set_xlabel('Signal Type')
    
    for index, row in avg_ret_by_signal.iterrows():
        chart.text(row.name, row.ret, round(row.ret, 2), color='black', ha="center")
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.boxplot(data=data[['high', 'low']], ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of daily high and low prices?')
    ax.legend(['High', 'Low'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
